    "guest": "None",
    "mmmCount": 12,
    "thatsGreatCount": 11,
    "notableMoments": "2nd Bonus Ep for Andor S1\n- Jason rewatched S1 on his phone, the way Tony Gilroy intended\n- The first 3 eps (Ferrix Hammers) were great, but these 3 really up the stakes\n- This show is about sacrifice - what are you willing to sacrifice to achieve the downfall of the empire? Luthen's pitch to Andor is so well-written\n- The Coruscant characters introduced in this arc - Syril's Mom, Mon Mothma, Diedre and the other ISB officers - are all incredible\n- Aldani - Ebon Moss-Bachrach is transcendent in this arc as Skeen - \"The Axe forgets but the Tree remembers\" and \"Trees. Pepper trees, centuries of them\"\n- Nemek - the manifesto is so resonant right now\n- We know the Empire is bad, but we haven't really seen the full impact of Imperial Tyranny until this show. \n- Incredible how they make a single tie fighter seem SO menacing. Proper contextualization of how dangerous these are",
