    "notableMoments": "We're Back - After some reservations with the 1st arc (1-3), the boys loved 4-6\n- Bix/Andor relationship back in the forefront - chemistry is incredible, and it ups the stakes for Andor\n- The Score - Demonstrably better in Eps 4-6\n- Much more complete view into life on Coruscant - Blade Runner vibes\n- Ghorman - Incredible production design, costumes, language - Total French Resistance vibes\n- Syril Karn thriving as a mole in the Ghorman Front (With Dedra as handler) \"Fascist Mommy who has her fastidious Sub with a praise kink\" - Jason\n- The Tension and Chaos is ramping up, and Luthen is starting to lose it, but Klea is stepping up\n- Saw Gerrera arc - Forrest Whitaker is doing the work. This shouldn't work but it does - Huffing Rydo\n- Andor under cover on Ghorman - He is looking smooth, and good at playing the part\n- Cinta and Vel arc - works with limited minutes on screen. Vel after Cinta death 'This is on you now, this is like skin'\n- The Party - Tension totally cranks up with Lonnie, Klea, Luthen, Mon, and Krennic. A great scene\n- Bix gets some revenge at the end - Cathartic\n- Things are rolling now",
