    "length": "2:24:48",
    "reviewer": "birria",
    "guest": "None",
    "mmmCount": 37,
    "thatsGreatCount": 18,
    "notableMoments": "\"The end of the greatest Star Wars, and possibly the greatest television that will ever exist\" - Jason\n- Next week pod will cover Rogue One (first time to revisit a movie)\n- The last 5 episodes of this show are perfect. So hard to stick the landing like this\n- \"I think we used up all the Perfect\"\n- Lonnie - This is the moment - Lonnie reveals the existance of the Death Star to the Rebellion. Lonnie doesn't get celebrated and hios contribution is not known\n- Luthen and Dedra at the shop is incredible - as good as Clooney and Tilda at the end of Michael Clayton - Just an All-Time scene\n- Dedra's obsession with Axis leads directly to the downfall of the ISB\n- Luthen Kleya Flashback Sequence intermixed with Kleya's assauklt on the hospital - God Tier TV\n- Krennic interrogating Dedra - Ben Mendelsohn just feasting in this scene\n- K2SO coming to the rescue in the apartment buildng - Like a horror movie\n- Mon finally gets her iconic haircut - evokes a Chandrillan wedding, cutting the hair to indicate the start of a new chapter\n- Andor and Vel's toast scene - emotional - 'I have friends everywhere\"\n- Nemek's manifesto would have spread so much farther if Haitch had produced it\n- Pardigaz last scene was a master class in simplicity as the ISB falls apart\n- Closing Montage - so satisfying - Vel and Mon, Kleya, Wilmon and his Ghorman girl, Perrin and the mob wife, Dedra on Narkina 3, and Andor walking to the U-Wing\n- And the closing tag with B2EMO, and Bix with the baby - Haitch was floored\n- Jason - We will never get a Star Wars this good again - Theymade something that was not for all 4 quadrants, that had a huge budget with all of the creative freedom in the world, that was never going to be for everyone",
