    "notableMoments": "The pod starts with \"What is Theater?\" and Kev responds with \"Theater is something that will break your heart, but then there's that one day where everything falls into place and you'll be chasing that feeling the rest of your life.\"\n- Turns out we are all theater geeks - Good talk about the strengths and weaknesses of Andrew Lloyd Webber\n- Jason really interested in the \"What is it like to be a human who is also divine?\" question\n- The fact that this is a passion play, and that it depicts Jewish characters as prominently to blame for killing Jesus, aligns with the staging of these throughout history to foment antisemitism\n- Duleck's Division - when Judas accepts 30 pieces of silver\n- Last supper fight between Jesus and Judas is the highlight of the whole show\n- The King Harrod song is \"the gayest song in musical history until The French Mistake in Blazing Saddles\"\n- \"Crucifixion seems real bad\" - Haitch\n- Letters - Lizzen, Bog Pod, Silly (Gethsemane but Chuckle Hut), Animal Mother, Mr Java, Truthsayer, Another vm from Haitch's re-designer Luke, Kev (live), Corey\n- Kev closes with \"Be hopeful, be kind, and be radical to each other\"",
